# Chainguard Libraries — JavaScript (reference template, NOT used by default).
#
# Understudy does NOT route local npm through Chainguard's mirror — see below.
# Production agent images still pull from Chainguard's rebuilt-from-source
# mirror, but via the Dockerfile `NPM_CHAINGUARD_AUTH` build-arg (see
# docs/chainguard-libraries.md §JavaScript), not via a root .npmrc.
#
# ── Why not a root .npmrc? ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Chainguard's npm mirror lags the public registry by days-to-weeks on fresh
# releases. npm has no multi-registry fallback primitive (unlike pip's
# `extra-index-url`) — scoped registries only help when the unmirrored
# package has a scope. Transitive deps with unscoped names (e.g.
# `posthog-node` pulled in by `@insforge/cli`) will 404 or ETARGET and
# there's no clean fallback, breaking dev ergonomics.
#
# Same pattern as pip: local dev uses public registries, Dockerfile enforces
# Chainguard at build time so shipped images are still rebuilt-from-source.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# If you DO want to force local npm through Chainguard (e.g. to verify
# which of your deps are mirrored), copy this template and live with the
# 404/ETARGET friction:
#
#   1. cp .npmrc.example .npmrc
#   2. chainctl auth pull-token --repository=javascript --ttl=720h
#   3. Fill {BASE64_OF_USERNAME_PASSWORD} with:
#        echo -n 'USERNAME:PASSWORD' | base64
#   4. .npmrc is .gitignored — never commit the real file.

registry=https://libraries.cgr.dev/javascript/
//libraries.cgr.dev/javascript/:_auth={BASE64_OF_USERNAME_PASSWORD}

# Scopes not mirrored by Chainguard — fall back to the public npm registry.
# Add more lines here as you hit them; symptom is a 404 on install.
@insforge:registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
@tinyfish:registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/
